Name: tooth agenesis
Definition: A tooth disease characterized by failure to develop on or more missing teeth.

Name: dental abscess
Definition: A tooth disease characterized by a localized collection of pus associated with a tooth.

Name: primary failure of tooth eruption
Definition: A tooth disease characterized by incomplete tooth eruption despite the presence of a clear eruption pathway that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in PTHR1 on chromosome 3p21.31.

Name: dental fluorosis
Definition: An uterine benign neoplasm that is characterized by the formation of gland-like structures

Name: anodontia
Definition: An uterine benign neoplasm that is characterized by the formation of gland-like structures
Synonym: Total anodontia of permanent and deciduous teeth

Name: teeth hard tissue disease
Definition: A central nervous system cancer develops from transformed cells of mesenchymal origin located_in brain and spine

Name: periodontal disease
Definition: A vaginitis that is characterized by a grayish vaginal discharge usually of foul odor and the presence of Gardnerella vaginalis.

Name: dentinogenesis imperfecta
Definition: A chordoma that derives_from the spine.

Name: periodontosis
Definition: A myopathy is characterized by progressive skeletal muscle weakness degeneration.
